summary:
The Security Council:

Recalling previous relevant resolutions, condemns the 14 February 2005 terrorist bombing and other attacks in Lebanon since October 2004, and reaffirms that those involved must be held accountable.

 Examining the report of the International Independent Investigation Commission (S/2006/375), it commends the Commission's professional work under difficult circumstances.

The Council:

1. Welcomes the Commission's report;
2. Extends the Commission's mandate until 15 June 2007;
3. Supports the Commission's intention to extend technical assistance to Lebanese authorities investigating other terrorist attacks since 1 October 2004;
4. Requests the Commission to report on the investigation's progress quarterly;
5. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
